Summary
The historical data of SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust (SPY) for the year of 2022 was used to develop the
equaon. Inially the data was loaded, the date column was converted from Object class to
DateTime class, and the summary stascs were checked.
As all columns have signicant standard deviaon greater than 0, we can use all the columns for
equaon. Then Intraday Volality which is equal to (High-Low)/Close along with daily volume
change and daily volality change were calculated and ploed.
We can see that, The volality delta value ranges from 0 to 0.05. Before building the equaons,
correlaon plot was ploed to check the inuence of variables.
We can see that volume has the highest inuence of 0.71 on volality which means if volume
increases the volality increases. Other variables have mild negave correlaon meaning if
Volality increases the other decreases. Linear Regression was used to build the mul variate
linear equaons using Volume, High, Low and Close.
Case 1: Using Equaon built using SPY on other ETFs and Stocks:
With the above built equaon, the Volality values predicted, and percentage of error was
calculated which is the absolute dierence between predicted and actual value divided by the
actual mes 100. Which gives the change between actual and predicted value. The actual and
predicted value were ploed.
From the plot we can say that the equaons t good for given data. The coecients and intercept
are of small value because the variables ranges are big whereas volality is always less than 1.
This equaon is then used on the same data but for 5 Year interval and its Percentage Error and
scaer plot were calculated and ploed.
The same equaon is ploed for other ETFs QQQ Invesco QQQ Trust Series I and VEA Vanguard
FTSE Developed Markets ETF and Stocks Google and Microso respecvely and the results were
noted down.

Results
We can see the equaon could not represent the actual value well and the mean percentage error
increases with dierent data. This might be since the equaon was largely inuenced by variable
Volume, if it was not as same SPY data then variaons in representaon arises and since the
volality in the dataset with which the equaon was built had values ranging from 0 to 0.06 values
with volality above them were represented accurately and if the data had small values, then also
the representaon produced by the equaon is wrong. The mean percentage error is small if the
data has similar values compared to SPY data. Another Shortcoming of this equaon is using
dependent variables such as High, Low, Close which had high dependencies within them.
